WEBVTT

00:03.138 --> 00:05.001
Welcome to the Life Church Podcast.

00:06.443 --> 00:13.114
We are an Acts 2 42 community, a family on a mission to bring a life of Jesus to warranty.

00:13.134 --> 00:21.066
We hope you're ready to hear what God has to say to you today through His Word and by His Spirit.

00:21.086 --> 00:24.071
So today I am bringing our Roman series to a close.

00:24.312 --> 00:26.795
Right, week one, Jeremy told us we are guilty.

00:27.957 --> 00:30.962
Week two, Helen told us Christ died for us.

00:31.266 --> 00:34.029
And Nick told us last week that we must respond.

00:34.390 --> 00:38.595
Sin, grace, confession.

00:39.576 --> 00:41.559
All leading the road to a promise.

00:42.320 --> 00:45.684
And Paul has been driving towards this moment from the very beginning of Romans.

00:46.905 --> 00:52.332
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved in Romans 10, 13.

00:52.412 --> 00:53.994
So let's all read that together, shall we?

00:55.036 --> 00:56.978
Everyone, come on, everyone.

00:57.154 --> 01:01.420
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

01:02.863 --> 01:08.912
Many of us believe we are saved by grace, but we live like we are on probation.

01:09.913 --> 01:20.048
Paul actually anticipated this struggle earlier in Romans, in Romans 5 he says, therefore, since we have been justified through faith, we have peace with God.

01:21.070 --> 01:23.994
He doesn't say we are working toward peace.

01:24.575 --> 01:26.578
He says we have peace.

01:26.818 --> 01:27.840
It's a past tense.

01:29.663 --> 01:33.989
Be honest, who here has ever had the thought, I'm just not good enough for God.

01:34.030 --> 01:34.610
Raise your hand.

01:36.794 --> 01:46.149
I definitely have that thought sounds humble, but actually it quietly assumes that salvation depends on your goodness in the first place.

01:48.172 --> 01:50.977
The gospel doesn't say you were almost good enough.

01:51.457 --> 01:54.322
It says Christ was completely sufficient.

01:56.546 --> 02:00.311
Paul has written one of the most freeing sentences in the entire Bible.

02:00.351 --> 02:04.095
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

02:05.077 --> 02:10.383
Not might be, not could be, not saved in probation, will be.

02:10.423 --> 02:13.267
Everyone say that, will be.

02:13.307 --> 02:15.610
Everyone.

02:16.911 --> 02:20.295
Paul begins with the most explosive word in that verse.

02:21.837 --> 02:22.418
Everyone.

02:23.810 --> 02:35.345
To a first century Jew, that word was disruptive, because it meant Gentiles, outsiders, former idol worshipers, people who, with complicated pasts, people who didn't grow up in church.

02:36.026 --> 02:44.777
And if you didn't grow up in church, if your journey has been messy, if you feel like you're the late addition to the family of faith, that word was written with you in mind.

02:46.479 --> 02:51.986
But everyone doesn't just remove cultural barriers, it removes emotional ones too.

02:52.770 --> 02:56.956
It destroys that religious presumption of, of course I'm saved.

02:57.116 --> 02:58.258
I've always been around this.

02:58.358 --> 02:59.800
I grew up in a Christian home.

02:59.820 --> 03:02.844
It destroys spiritual despair.

03:02.884 --> 03:05.268
There's no way God could love me.

03:05.308 --> 03:07.030
He'd never want someone like me.

03:07.090 --> 03:11.336
Because if you think you deserve salvation, you don't.

03:14.140 --> 03:19.347
If you think you're disqualified from salvation, you're not.

03:19.367 --> 03:21.170
That word, everyone,

03:21.730 --> 03:24.273
levels the ground at the foot of the cross.

03:25.414 --> 03:29.198
No VIP line, no back entrance, no spiritual CV required.

03:30.540 --> 03:33.283
But this wasn't a new idea that Paul invented.

03:33.323 --> 03:38.929
In Joel 2.32 we read, everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

03:40.010 --> 03:46.638
Paul is quoting a prophet who spoke to people in crisis, invasion, fear, national collapse.

03:47.299 --> 03:50.322
And God's answer wasn't fix it yourselves.

03:51.394 --> 03:54.698
It was, call on me.

03:55.519 --> 03:59.944
The invitation has always been wider than people expected.

03:59.964 --> 04:02.527
And that includes to all of you.

04:02.567 --> 04:09.556
Three Romans, Paul has spent chapters taking us into deep theological waters.

04:10.257 --> 04:20.069
Predestination, calling, justification, glorification, he stretches our minds with a God who foreknew, predestined, called, justified, and glorified.

04:20.109 --> 04:21.330
It's big.

04:21.634 --> 04:22.415
It's waiting.

04:22.976 --> 04:23.958
It's God-sized.

04:24.619 --> 04:27.263
And then he turns and it's almost disarmingly.

04:27.283 --> 04:30.327
He says, everyone who calls.

04:32.090 --> 04:32.671
Who calls?

04:33.572 --> 04:34.534
Do you see what he's doing?

04:34.954 --> 04:39.241
God's sovereignty does not cancel human invitation.

04:40.483 --> 04:43.828
The God who ordains the ends also ordains the means.

04:44.589 --> 04:46.351
The door is not locked from the inside.

04:46.932 --> 04:47.433
It's open.

04:49.716 --> 04:50.738
John Wesley.

04:50.818 --> 04:56.085
The founder of Methodism used a simple picture to describe salvation, a house.

04:57.327 --> 05:00.311
He said, salvation is like approaching a house with three parts.

05:01.993 --> 05:02.955
First, there's the porch.

05:03.656 --> 05:04.957
That's where grace meets us.

05:06.720 --> 05:15.271
The grace that goes before, it's that stirring in your heart, that sense that maybe you need God, that moment when you realize, I can't fix this on my own.

05:16.213 --> 05:20.178
You're not inside yet, but you're not far away either.

05:20.514 --> 05:22.417
You're standing on the porch, aware.

05:22.477 --> 05:24.841
Then there's the door.

05:26.063 --> 05:27.164
The door is faith.

05:27.184 --> 05:28.487
The door is justification.

05:29.128 --> 05:32.913
The door is the moment you step through and trust Christ.

05:33.434 --> 05:36.499
Not just intellectually, but personally.

05:36.559 --> 05:40.205
You stop admiring the house from the outside and you walk in.

05:41.787 --> 05:43.029
Then there's the house itself.

05:44.752 --> 05:46.034
That sanctification.

05:46.722 --> 05:53.730
That's the long, beautiful process of growing, stumbling, learning obedience, becoming more like Jesus.

05:54.812 --> 05:56.113
The daily life with Him.

05:57.895 --> 05:59.457
But here's the part I don't want you to miss.

06:00.218 --> 06:01.700
The door is open.

06:02.601 --> 06:03.662
Can everyone say that together?

06:03.703 --> 06:05.565
The door is open.

06:05.625 --> 06:09.189
The porch exists because there's a door.

06:10.471 --> 06:13.234
No one stands on the porch of a boarded-up house, do they?

06:15.522 --> 06:24.713
Maybe it was a conversation that wouldn't leave your mind or a moment when worship suddenly felt personal, you felt all the emotions come in.

06:25.754 --> 06:27.336
That wasn't a coincidence.

06:28.197 --> 06:34.345
Jesus says in John 644, no one comes to me unless the Father draws them.

06:35.867 --> 06:42.034
Even your curiosity about God is evidence of grace already at work.

06:44.418 --> 06:46.221
You didn't wonder toward God alone.

06:46.822 --> 06:47.943
You were being welcomed.

06:50.908 --> 06:54.393
Paul says, everyone who calls in the name of the Lord.

06:56.276 --> 06:59.461
That phrase reaches back into the Old Testament.

06:59.481 --> 07:02.986
To call in the name wasn't about reciting a formula.

07:03.667 --> 07:08.374
It meant appealing to somebody's character, entrusting yourself to who they are.

07:09.075 --> 07:10.958
It's not a technique, it's trust.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.842
It's not about saying the right words.

07:14.178 --> 07:15.520
It's about surrender.

07:15.580 --> 07:19.225
Have you ever tried to pray the right prayer?

07:19.285 --> 07:23.171
Like if you could just arrange the words perfectly, God would respond faster.

07:24.393 --> 07:26.215
Like heaven is waiting for proper grammar.

07:26.896 --> 07:28.238
I wouldn't do very well if that would try.

07:32.204 --> 07:38.413
If your car broke down, you wouldn't call a roadside assistance and explain how an engine worked, would you?

07:38.974 --> 07:40.676
You'd say, I need help.

07:41.397 --> 07:41.938
That's it.

07:43.298 --> 07:46.602
Some of us might try and sound a bit spiritual though, wouldn't they?

07:46.662 --> 07:51.086
We'd say like, Lord, if it aligns with your sovereign mechanical purposes.

07:53.409 --> 07:58.274
Meanwhile, heaven is saying, you can just say help.

08:00.657 --> 08:07.805
Salvation begins not when you impress God with your knowledge, but when you admit you can't rescue yourself.

08:08.846 --> 08:09.787
That's what calling is.

08:10.488 --> 08:12.690
It's not polished, it's surrendered.

08:14.434 --> 08:17.378
I want you to just think about the thief on the cross in Luke 23.

08:18.901 --> 08:23.428
Then he said, which is a thief, Jesus remember me when you come into your kingdom.

08:23.908 --> 08:28.155
And Jesus answered him, truly I tell you, today you will be with me in paradise.

08:30.118 --> 08:31.820
He didn't pray a polished prayer.

08:32.602 --> 08:34.084
He didn't have time to prove anything.

08:34.124 --> 08:36.928
He just said, Jesus remember me.

08:36.988 --> 08:39.732
And Jesus responded immediately.

08:39.793 --> 08:43.378
This is what I find

08:43.522 --> 08:44.483
quite remarkable.

08:44.543 --> 09:01.921
The thief had no time for spiritual improvement, no baptism class, no server team, no opportunity to prove transformation, which meant his salvation rested entirely on Christ, not progress.

09:03.522 --> 09:07.106
I think this story exists so nobody can say I came too late.

09:09.348 --> 09:11.090
It's just grace.

09:14.466 --> 09:18.011
I want you to turn to the person next to you and say, it's not about performance.

09:22.217 --> 09:24.761
Now I want you to say, it's about dependence.

09:28.746 --> 09:32.872
The power of the call is not in the strength of your voice.

09:33.533 --> 09:37.058
It's in the reliability of the one you're calling.

09:37.098 --> 09:42.386
If you're drowning, you wouldn't stay drowning,

09:42.658 --> 09:44.861
to negotiate a rescue strategy, would you?

09:44.921 --> 09:46.283
You'd just reach.

09:48.305 --> 09:51.829
We often evaluate our salvation by the intensity of our prayers.

09:51.889 --> 09:59.499
Oh, by the works we do, God evaluates it by the sufficiency of his son.

10:02.182 --> 10:05.747
The third part of that verse will be saved.

10:08.090 --> 10:11.634
Why does certainty make us feel uncomfortable?

10:13.570 --> 10:18.737
Is it because everywhere else in life security depends on performance?

10:18.757 --> 10:19.699
Jobs can be lost.

10:20.239 --> 10:21.461
Relationships can break.

10:22.623 --> 10:23.925
Promises can get broken.

10:25.807 --> 10:28.952
So we project that instability onto God.

10:30.013 --> 10:32.497
But I want you to listen to how Paul builds in here.

10:33.278 --> 10:34.359
So it's going to be up on the screen.

10:34.399 --> 10:36.242
Romans 8, 28.

10:37.602 --> 10:43.629
And we know that in all things God works for the good of those who love him, who have been called according to his purpose.

10:44.830 --> 10:55.501
For those God fondue, he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his son, that he might be the firstborn among many brothers and sisters, and those he predestined he also called.

10:56.022 --> 10:57.724
Those he called he also justified.

10:58.385 --> 11:00.427
Those he justified he also glorified.

11:01.047 --> 11:03.350
What then shall we say in response to these things?

11:04.071 --> 11:07.154
If God is for us, who can be against us?

11:07.970 --> 11:12.536
He who did not spare his own son, but gave him up for all of us.

11:13.377 --> 11:17.322
How will he not also, along with him, graciously give us all things?

11:18.884 --> 11:21.908
Who will bring any charge against those whom God has chosen?

11:21.968 --> 11:24.391
It is God who justifies.

11:25.592 --> 11:27.074
Who then is the one who condemns?

11:27.635 --> 11:28.035
No one.

11:29.177 --> 11:33.202
Christ Jesus who died, more than that, who was raised to life

11:33.410 --> 11:37.777
is at the right hand of God and is also interceding for us.

11:38.978 --> 11:52.298
He shall separate us from the love of God, shall trouble or hardship or persecution or famine or nakedness or danger or sword, as it is written, for your sake we face death all day long.

11:52.939 --> 11:54.942
We consider the sheep to be slaughtered.

11:54.982 --> 12:00.210
No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.

12:00.674 --> 12:17.615
for I am convinced that neither death nor life nor angels nor demons neither present nor the future nor any power neither height nor depth or anything else in all creation will ever be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.

12:17.655 --> 12:21.300
He justifies God does.

12:21.340 --> 12:24.044
He condemns no one.

12:24.584 --> 12:26.407
He separates nothing.

12:27.548 --> 12:28.169
Now you say it.

12:28.269 --> 12:29.170
He justifies.

12:30.434 --> 12:31.115
Who condemns?

12:32.417 --> 12:33.178
Who separates?

12:35.301 --> 12:40.870
If you could lose your salvation through your weakness, you would have to be stronger than God's grip.

12:41.410 --> 12:44.876
Imagine if this only works when you drove perfectly.

12:46.518 --> 12:50.825
Imagine this is a seatbelt, not a plain seatbelt.

12:50.845 --> 12:59.858
Imagine if it only locked when you stayed in your lane, only when you never drifted, only when you never made a mistake.

13:00.770 --> 13:01.671
Would you feel safe?

13:04.094 --> 13:04.755
Of course you wouldn't.

13:05.896 --> 13:08.139
Because that defeats the entire purpose.

13:08.820 --> 13:11.683
This is not designed for perfect drivers.

13:13.485 --> 13:15.688
It is designed for collisions.

13:16.629 --> 13:18.972
It is designed for sudden stops.

13:20.073 --> 13:22.336
It's designed for the moment you don't see coming.

13:24.138 --> 13:30.386
You don't sit in your driveway in the morning and think, I'm just going to crash gently to see if it still works.

13:31.522 --> 13:36.589
You trust what was engineered before you ever turned the key.

13:39.493 --> 13:42.017
You don't buckle up because you're confident in your driving.

13:43.178 --> 13:46.203
You buckle up because you know you're human.

13:47.484 --> 13:50.409
Salvation is not a reward for steadily driving.

13:51.710 --> 13:54.494
It is security for floor drivers.

13:56.778 --> 13:59.922
If this only worked when you didn't need it, it wouldn't be safety.

14:02.658 --> 14:07.524
And if grace only worked when you were strong, it wouldn't be grace.

14:09.747 --> 14:12.951
Some of you might be living that the seatbelt only activates on your good days.

14:16.735 --> 14:21.921
Like it only tightens it when you've read enough of your Bible.

14:23.724 --> 14:26.026
Like it locks when you pray long enough.

14:27.448 --> 14:29.190
Like it releases if you start to doubt.

14:30.732 --> 14:32.274
But that's not how this works.

14:33.922 --> 14:36.905
This bell doesn't ask how well you drove this week.

14:39.668 --> 14:42.610
It simply holds when impact comes.

14:45.273 --> 14:46.174
And listen carefully.

14:48.056 --> 14:51.159
The cross was not installed because you're a careful driver.

14:51.179 --> 14:55.323
It was installed because God knew you weren't.

14:56.844 --> 15:02.930
And if you could fall out of salvation every time you failed, then the cross would be weaker than your sin.

15:04.930 --> 15:09.878
And it's not.

15:09.898 --> 15:12.181
You are not secured because you perform well.

15:13.383 --> 15:16.248
You are secured because Christ finished the work.

15:17.730 --> 15:26.744
And when life gets hard, when you stumble, when you doubt, when you sin and feels ashamed, grace doesn't disengage.

15:27.966 --> 15:28.627
It holds.

15:30.369 --> 15:33.394
When Jesus said it is finished, he meant it.

15:34.338 --> 15:36.621
Finished means the work is settled.

15:37.943 --> 15:39.505
We grow from that foundation.

15:39.865 --> 15:41.187
We don't rebuild it every week.

15:42.288 --> 15:43.570
Yes, we repent.

15:44.070 --> 15:45.152
Yes, we fight sin.

15:45.632 --> 15:46.554
Yes, we grow.

15:46.594 --> 15:52.401
But we do it from security, not for security.

15:53.582 --> 15:56.086
When you fall, you don't fall out of his hand.

15:56.767 --> 15:57.728
You fall into it.

16:01.032 --> 16:02.674
Let me just say something gently.

16:03.714 --> 16:04.275
but clearly.

16:06.198 --> 16:07.220
Some of you are tired.

16:07.260 --> 16:15.613
Not because following Jesus is heavy, but because you're trying to carry something he's already carried.

16:18.537 --> 16:19.940
Grace offens us.

16:25.569 --> 16:28.413
I want you to think about the older brother in Luke 15.

16:28.433 --> 16:31.538
The prodigal comes home

16:32.450 --> 16:35.113
Celebration begins and the older brother is angry.

16:35.173 --> 16:36.315
Why?

16:36.355 --> 16:42.742
Because grace, given freely, feels unfair to people trying to earn belongings.

16:43.663 --> 16:46.747
So when the protocol comes home, the father says, all I have is yours.

16:49.049 --> 16:51.312
We would rather contribute than receive.

16:51.933 --> 16:54.676
We'd rather say, I'm saved because I've been consistent.

16:55.377 --> 16:56.839
I'm saved because I serve.

16:57.399 --> 16:59.762
I'm saved because I'm not like how I used to be.

17:00.450 --> 17:02.673
I'm saved because I try harder than most.

17:03.575 --> 17:04.696
That feels safer, right?

17:06.399 --> 17:10.585
Because if I contribute to it, then I can control it.

17:11.747 --> 17:14.851
If I help build it, then I can help protect it.

17:16.334 --> 17:22.463
But Grace says you bought nothing to the table except the sin that made it necessary.

17:22.483 --> 17:24.966
And that kind of stings.

17:26.689 --> 17:30.194
Have you ever tried to pay for dinner and then somebody says, now I've got it?

17:30.434 --> 17:32.636
And then there's that awkward tension and you reach for your wallet.

17:32.656 --> 17:33.237
Are you sure?

17:34.358 --> 17:34.678
Why?

17:34.718 --> 17:36.800
Because receiving feels vulnerable.

17:38.462 --> 17:39.923
Receiving admits need.

17:40.324 --> 17:42.326
Receiving means you cannot repay.

17:42.366 --> 17:45.088
Now multiply that by eternity.

17:46.290 --> 17:47.671
Salvation is like that.

17:50.153 --> 17:51.595
Except the cost wasn't a meal.

17:52.936 --> 17:53.617
It was the cross.

17:55.379 --> 17:58.802
If Christ paid the full price, you cannot add to it.

18:01.154 --> 18:04.597
But if you cannot add to it, you cannot subtract from it.

18:05.678 --> 18:09.662
You are saved because Christ is faithful, not because you are steady.

18:12.305 --> 18:13.986
I just want to talk about works for a moment.

18:14.006 --> 18:15.948
This came up at Life Group the other day.

18:15.968 --> 18:19.111
In James 2, it says, faith without works is dead.

18:20.472 --> 18:22.294
Yes, works matter.

18:23.295 --> 18:25.677
But works are evidence, not payment.

18:27.259 --> 18:29.281
Fruit does not make the tree alive.

18:30.262 --> 18:30.802
Life

18:30.914 --> 18:31.835
produces fruit.

18:33.037 --> 18:35.880
Salvation is the moment God declares you righteous.

18:36.621 --> 18:40.906
Sanctification is the lifetime he spends making you look like it.

18:41.867 --> 18:44.491
Salvation frees you from sin's penalty.

18:45.252 --> 18:47.715
Sanctification frees you from its power.

18:47.775 --> 18:51.359
One is a verdict, the other is transformation.

18:52.120 --> 18:54.763
And if you mix them up, you will live your life exhausted.

18:54.823 --> 19:00.370
If you try to sanctify yourself enough to feel saved, you will never rest.

19:00.898 --> 19:03.461
because you will always see what needs fixing.

19:04.683 --> 19:09.569
But when you understand that salvation comes first, that verdict is already in.

19:09.609 --> 19:14.755
Then obedience stops being a desperate attempt to earn love.

19:16.056 --> 19:19.541
It becomes a grateful response to love already given.

19:20.922 --> 19:24.887
We grow from security, not for it.

19:26.189 --> 19:28.171
But assurance is not permission to sin.

19:29.373 --> 19:30.514
It's power to fight it.

19:32.962 --> 19:33.923
Let me just bring this in.

19:34.924 --> 19:38.909
Picture a child crossing a busy road holding her father's hand.

19:40.130 --> 19:41.051
She might feel small.

19:41.812 --> 19:42.553
She might stumble.

19:42.953 --> 19:44.895
She might wonder if she's holding tight enough.

19:46.077 --> 19:50.902
But her safety does not depend on the strength of her grip.

19:50.922 --> 19:51.743
It depends on his.

19:53.124 --> 20:01.874
Isaiah 41 says, for I am the Lord your God who takes hold of your right hand and says to you, do not fear I will help you.

20:03.746 --> 20:05.308
God doesn't say, hold tighter.

20:05.848 --> 20:08.651
He says, I am holding you.

20:10.292 --> 20:13.596
Because your safety was never in your grip.

20:15.077 --> 20:17.019
It was always in his hand.

20:18.681 --> 20:24.266
Parents, when your child grabs your hand in a traffic, who is actually responsible, you are.

20:25.467 --> 20:32.274
And the gospel says this, everyone who calls will be saved.

20:33.314 --> 20:39.704
not might be, not until they mess up, not as long as they perform, will be.

20:39.744 --> 20:50.340
Not because you prayed perfectly, not because you've had a good month, not because you've attended church, but because Christ finished the work.

20:52.163 --> 20:59.314
And according to Romans 8, nothing, not death, not life, not your past, not your failure, not your anxiety, nothing.

21:00.322 --> 21:03.287
can separate you from the love of God in Christ Jesus.

21:04.589 --> 21:05.270
So hear me.

21:06.552 --> 21:14.564
If you have called on him, stop resentencing yourself to a crime God has already pardoned.

21:15.947 --> 21:19.452
Stop trying to repay a debt that's already been cleared.

21:20.834 --> 21:23.899
Stop living like the cross was a down payment.

21:24.841 --> 21:28.306
It was full payment, rest,

21:29.282 --> 21:30.724
And if you haven't called, call.

21:32.706 --> 21:35.229
Not with impressive words, but with honesty.

21:36.190 --> 21:41.035
Because Emmanuel, God with us, is not waiting for you to become impressive.

21:42.016 --> 21:43.698
He's waiting for you to surrender.

21:45.600 --> 21:49.084
And when you call, you will be saved.

21:50.466 --> 21:52.047
The door is open.

21:53.149 --> 21:55.151
And even when you stumble afterward, remember this.

21:56.012 --> 21:57.874
You don't fall out of his hand.

21:58.946 --> 22:03.356
You fall in it.

22:03.376 --> 22:04.900
We've come to the end of this week's message.

